Nigerian music superster finally throws in the towel

Popular Nigerian musician, David Adeleke, alias Davido, has reacted to the arrest of his uncle, Senator Ademola Adeleke, by the Nigeria Police. 
Following the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) governorship candidate in Osun State that was arrested on Monday evening.
Davido, on his Instagram page, said he has given up on democracy in Nigeria. Alongside a picture of the report, Davido wrote: ”I give up on Democracy.”
Force spokesman, Mr. Frank Mba, explained that Adeleke was picked up for a criminal offence.
 

			
